Subject: re: need help finding a screwdriver bit, also Insulation

You may be doomed - while you can get bit sets, the only ones I know of that you can buy a bunch of is the #2 phillips.  I have a strange feeling (may be wrong) that there is something unusual about the bits which hold them in place - you may have to replace the whole unit for the lack of 2 bits (or in this case, one bit). ;-)

You can also try something like MCSDirect, oer some other outfit that has electricians tools - I think that's who I found my bit for my Yankee Screwdriver with.  Good luck.

Obligatory Bus Content - Why not use something like brass expanded metal screen for the insulation hold-up - it doesn't rust and will drain.  However, remembering the old wall soundproofing ceiling tiles back then (remember the white stuff with the 1/8" hoes?), it may have served a similar purpose - I have yet to find something that VW-Werke did that didn't cover at least 2 or 3 bases to accomplish something.

Susanne



